## Quick Revision Points
- Projects prove practical skill — pick based on your level: lab setup → vulnerability assessment → full pentest simulation.
- Always structure projects like a real report: objective, setup, methodology, findings, remediation, conclusion.
- Only ever test systems you own or are explicitly authorized to test (lab VMs, TryHackMe/HackTheBox, DVWA/Metasploitable).
- Document and showcase projects publicly (GitHub, portfolio) with diagrams — this is what makes a resume stand out in cybersecurity hiring.
